DOCUMENT();

loadMacros(
"PG.pl",
"PGbasicmacros.pl",
"PGchoicemacros.pl",
"PGanswermacros.pl",
"PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl"
);

$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a = random(3,8,1);
$b= $a;
while($b==$a){$b = random(2,8,1);}
$c = $b;
while($b==$c){$c = random(2,8,1);}
$coeff1 = $a-$b;
$coeff2 = $a+$b;

TEXT(&beginproblem);
BEGIN_TEXT
\setlength{\unitlength}{0.5in}
\begin{picture}(4,4)(-.5,-.5)
\thicklines
\put(.4,0){\line(0,1){1.2}}
\put(.4,0){\line(1,0){1.5}}
\put(.4,1.2){\line(1,0){1.5}}
\put(1.9,0){\line(0,1){1.2}}
\put(.4,0){\circle*{.1}}
\thinlines
\put(-.5,0){\vector(1,0){4}}
\put(0,-.5){\vector(0,1){4}}
\put(-.167,-.5){\line(1,3){1.167}}
\put(1,3){\line(1,-2){1.75}}
\put(.3,-.3){\((u,0)\)}
\end{picture}

$BR
The bottom edge of a rectangle is on the positive \(x\)-axis. The other
two vertices are on the graph of
\[y = $coeff1 x + $c - | $coeff2 x - $c | \]
Find the maximum possible area of such a rectangle.

$PAR
To solve this problem, we let \((u,0)\) denote the bottom left vertex of
the rectangle.  Then the top right vertex of the rectangle is at
$BR
\((\)\{ans_rule(25)\} \(,\) \{ans_rule(25)\}\()\)
$BR
(Your answers should be expressions in \(u\).)
$BR
Thus the area of the rectangle is the following function of \(u\):
$BR
\{ans_rule(35)\}
$BR
This function has a critical point at
\(u=\) \{ans_rule(25)\}
$BR
We conclude that the maximum possible area of such a rectangle is:
$BR
\{ans_rule(35)\}
END_TEXT

$ans1 = "($c - $a*u)/$b";
$ans2 = "2*$a*u";
$ans3 = "$ans2*($ans1 - u)";
$ans4 = $c/(2*($a+$b));
$s = ($c - $a*$ans4)/$b;
$ans5 = 2*$a*$ans4*($s - $ans4);

&ANS(function_cmp($ans1,"u"));
&ANS(function_cmp($ans2,"u"));
&ANS(function_cmp($ans3,"u"));
&ANS(std_num_cmp($ans4));
&ANS(std_num_cmp($ans5));

ENDDOCUMENT();
